======================================================================
1. RANKING ENTROPY: S(T) = log₂(H(T))
======================================================================
  H(T)/n! = fraction of total orderings consistent with T
  S(T) = log₂(H(T)) = 'ranking entropy' in bits
  Maximum: S_max = log₂(n!) for transitive (all orderings work) — WRONG
  Actually: H(transitive) = 1, so S_min = 0
  H(regular) = max → S_max = log₂(H_max)

  n=3:
    S_min = log₂(1) = 0.0000 bits
    S_max = log₂(3) = 1.5850 bits
    S_mean = log₂(E[H]) = log₂(1.50) = 0.5850 bits
    S_max/log₂(n!) = 0.6131
    Shannon entropy of H-value distribution: 0.8113 bits
    Max possible (log₂ of distinct H values): 1.0000

  n=4:
    S_min = log₂(1) = 0.0000 bits
    S_max = log₂(5) = 2.3219 bits
    S_mean = log₂(E[H]) = log₂(3.00) = 1.5850 bits
    S_max/log₂(n!) = 0.5064
    Shannon entropy of H-value distribution: 1.5613 bits
    Max possible (log₂ of distinct H values): 1.5850

  n=5:
    S_min = log₂(1) = 0.0000 bits
    S_max = log₂(15) = 3.9069 bits
    S_mean = log₂(E[H]) = log₂(7.50) = 2.9069 bits
    S_max/log₂(n!) = 0.5657
    Shannon entropy of H-value distribution: 2.6810 bits
    Max possible (log₂ of distinct H values): 2.8074

======================================================================
2. NOISY CHANNEL: TOURNAMENT AS PAIRWISE COMPARISON CHANNEL
======================================================================
  Model: n items have a true ranking π ∈ S_n
  Channel: each pair (i,j) compared independently
    Correct comparison w.p. p > 1/2, error w.p. 1-p
  Output: tournament T
  H(T) = # rankings consistent with T
  Channel capacity: how many bits of ranking info per comparison?
  p=0.51: E[H]=7.50, I(π;T)=4.3516 bits, efficiency=0.4352 bits/comparison
  p=0.60: E[H]=7.20, I(π;T)=4.4334 bits, efficiency=0.4433 bits/comparison
  p=0.70: E[H]=6.33, I(π;T)=4.6900 bits, efficiency=0.4690 bits/comparison
  p=0.80: E[H]=4.93, I(π;T)=5.1479 bits, efficiency=0.5148 bits/comparison
  p=0.90: E[H]=3.11, I(π;T)=5.8585 bits, efficiency=0.5858 bits/comparison
  p=0.95: E[H]=2.08, I(π;T)=6.3335 bits, efficiency=0.6333 bits/comparison
  p=1.00: E[H]=1.00, I(π;T)=6.9069 bits, efficiency=0.6907 bits/comparison

  Maximum I(π;T) = log₂(5!) = 6.9069 bits
  With 10 comparisons → max 0.6907 bits/comparison

