6. SOURCE CODING: ENTROPY vs TEMPERATURE
======================================================================
  n=5: Tournament source at temperature T = 1/β
  P(T) ∝ exp(β·H(T))
  Source entropy S(β) = -Σ P(T) log₂ P(T)
  β=  0.001: S= 10.00 bits, <H>=  7.52, n_eff=  1024.0, S/m=1.0000
  β=  0.010: S= 10.00 bits, <H>=  7.68, n_eff=  1023.1, S/m=0.9999
  β=  0.100: S=  9.88 bits, <H>=  9.25, n_eff=   939.3, S/m=0.9875
  β=  0.500: S=  8.40 bits, <H>= 13.22, n_eff=   336.8, S/m=0.8396
  β=  1.000: S=  7.16 bits, <H>= 14.46, n_eff=   142.7, S/m=0.7157
  β=  2.000: S=  6.25 bits, <H>= 14.93, n_eff=    76.0, S/m=0.6249
  β=  5.000: S=  6.00 bits, <H>= 15.00, n_eff=    64.1, S/m=0.6001
  β= 10.000: S=  6.00 bits, <H>= 15.00, n_eff=    64.0, S/m=0.6000
  β= 50.000: S=  6.00 bits, <H>= 15.00, n_eff=    64.0, S/m=0.6000

  Phase transition analysis:
    Steepest entropy drop at β_c ≈ 0.311 (T_c ≈ 3.216)

