7. KOLMOGOROV COMPLEXITY vs RANKING AMBIGUITY
======================================================================
  Conjecture: K(T) and H(T) are ANTI-correlated
  Simple tournaments (low K) tend to have extreme H
  Complex tournaments (high K) tend to have middling H
  bits=   0: H=  1, runs=1, RLE=5, SC=False, scores=(np.int64(0), np.int64(1), np.int64(2), np.int64(3), np.int64(4)), Var=2.00
