======================================================================
8. FISHER INFORMATION: SCORE AS SUFFICIENT STATISTIC
======================================================================
  Score sequence s = (s_1,...,s_n) is a statistic of T
  By THM-163: H_2 = c_2 · n · (m - 2·Var(s))
  Score is 'almost sufficient' for H (85-100% info captured)

  Fisher information I_F(θ) = Var(∂logP/∂θ) measures info content
  For exponential family P(T) ∝ exp(β·H(T)):
    I_F(β) = Var_β[H(T)] = <H²> - <H>²

  n=5: Fisher information I_F(β) = Var_β[H]
  β=0.01: <H>=7.68, Var[H]=17.8459, I_F=0.0018
        Var[score_var]=0.2967, Fisher ratio: 0.0166 (=1 if score sufficient)
  β=0.10: <H>=9.25, Var[H]=16.6019, I_F=0.1660
        Var[score_var]=0.2463, Fisher ratio: 0.0148 (=1 if score sufficient)
  β=0.50: <H>=13.22, Var[H]=4.7299, I_F=1.1825
        Var[score_var]=0.0537, Fisher ratio: 0.0114 (=1 if score sufficient)
  β=1.00: <H>=14.46, Var[H]=1.1851, I_F=1.1851
        Var[score_var]=0.0348, Fisher ratio: 0.0294 (=1 if score sufficient)
  β=2.00: <H>=14.93, Var[H]=0.1385, I_F=0.5540
        Var[score_var]=0.0370, Fisher ratio: 0.2670 (=1 if score sufficient)
